  abstract = {J. Milnor recently introduced the local Picard-Lefschetz-monodromy of an isolated singularity of a hypersurface. This is an important tool in the investigation of the topology of singularities. The monodromy is an action on a certain cohomology group and is defined in topological terms. In this paper we find an algebraic description of the monodromy. We construct by algebraic methods a regular singular ordinary linear differential operator, such that the monodromy of this singular operator coincides with the Picard-Lefschetz monodromy. As an application we prove that the eigenvalues of the monodromy are roots of unity. Our treatment is close in spirit to Grothendiecks theory of the Gau{$\beta$}-Manin-connection.},
