  url = {https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0001870889900297},
  urldate = {2022-06-07},
  abstract = {Let F be an ordered field, and let p denote the family of all convex polytopes in the d-dimensional vector space V over F. The universal abelian group {$\prod$} corresponding to the translation invariant valuations on p has generators [P] for P {$\epsilon$} p (with [{$\oslash$}] = 0), satisfying the relations (V) [P {$\smile$} Q] + [P {$\frown$}] = [P] + [Q] whenever P, Q, P {$\smile$} Q {$\epsilon$} p, and (T) [P + t] = [P] for P {$\epsilon$} p and t{$\epsilon$}V. With multiplication induced by (M) [P] {$\cdot$} [Q] = [P + Q], {$\prod$} is almost a graded commutative algebra over F, in that {$\prod$} = {$\oplus$}dr = 0{$\Xi$}r, with {$\Xi$}0 {$\cong$} Z, {$\Xi$}r a vector space over F (r {$\geq$} 1), and {$\Xi$}r {$\cdot$} {$\Xi$}s = {$\Xi$}r + s (r, s {$\geq$} 0, {$\Xi$}r = \textbraceleft 0\textbraceright{} forr {$>$} d). The dilatation (D) {$\Delta$}({$\lambda$})[P] = [{$\lambda$}P] for P {$\epsilon$} p and {$\lambda$} {$\epsilon$} F is such that {$\Delta$}({$\lambda$})x = {$\lambda$}rx for x{$\epsilon\Xi$}r and {$\lambda$} {$\geq$} 0. Negative dilatations arise from the Euler map (E) [P] {$\mapsto$} [P]{$\ast$} := {$\sum$}F (-1)dimF [F] (the sum extending over all faces F of P), since {$\Delta$}({$\lambda$})x = {$\lambda$}rx{$\ast$} for x{$\epsilon\Xi$}r and {$\lambda$} {$<$} 0. Separating group homomorphisms for {$\prod$} are the frame functionals, which give the volumes of the faces of polytopes determined by successive support hyperplanes in sequences of directions. Two isomorphisms on {$\prod$} are described: one related to cones of outer normal vectors, and the other to the polytope groups, obtained from {$\prod$} by discarding polytopes of dimension less than d. Various applications of the polytope algebra are given, including a theory of mixed polytopes, which has implications for mixed valuations.},
  langid = {english},
  timestamp = {2026-06-10T17:53:59Z},
  file = {McM89_content_list.json:/home/dzack/Zotero/storage/3478R3KF/[McMullen 1989] The polytope algebra_content_list.json:application/json;McM89_middle.json:/home/dzack/Zotero/storage/3NKBSUWZ/[McMullen 1989] The polytope algebra_middle.json:application/json;McM89_extracted.md:/home/dzack/Zotero/storage/5YBR5MBL/[McMullen 1989] The polytope algebra.md:text/markdown;[McMullen 1989] The polytope algebra:/home/dzack/Zotero/storage/AMS6TAIN/[McMullen 1989] The polytope algebra.pdf:application/pdf}
